stylometry: Decision trees are important in problem solving because it is a diagram that shows you all the possible outcomes for different sittuations. It keeps everything organized and easy to follow while showing a large amount of information.They are used by breaking down the information into sections with all the possible outcomes. A decision tree can be used to solve a problem such as which car to buy. You would start of with a single line saying you want to buy a car. Then branch off the the different types of cars you would like to purchase. Then from each car you could make more branches listing each possitive and negative about each car. By doing this and looking at the decision tree you could easily see which car had the most possitives and negatives helping you make the final decision.
